title: Bug 121170 - getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings
description: The current bug report lacks a detailed description of the issue, reproduction steps, and observed and expected behavior. The issue seems to be related to the getColumnLabel() method not returning user recognizable strings before and after data extraction. We need to provide more context and clarity to resolve this bug.
OB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() is returning different labels before and after data extraction.
EB: Bug 121170 - The IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method should consistently return the same user recognizable labels before and after data extraction.
SR:
To reproduce the bug:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
3. Compare the labels retrieved in steps 1 and 2. They should be the same, but currently, they are different.
